{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"50c1ef8d-8352-4950-9500-723d10537ec3","content":"For a .NET Web API, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD single-tenant (organizational) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD multi-tenant |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Example with Azure AD single-org:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer auth without Azure AD, use `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nRun `dotnet new webapi --help` to see all available options for your installed SDK version.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7a166a6c-8c12-4434-a567-a7e692aab1fc","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET development question. Let me check if there's relevant content in the repository that might help answer this, particularly in the plugins directory.\n\nActually, looking at the context - this is a general question about creating a web API project with authentication. I don't need to search the codebase for this - it's a knowledge question about .NET templates (likely, given the repository context mentions dotnet plugins).\n\nLet me give a concise answer based on my knowledge of .NET templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":375,"requestId":"7403:300A76:1B692BB:1E6847E:69FA8F76"},"id":"9bde364d-e78a-4f6c-a01c-2d42102c4f80","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:46:55.706Z","parentId":"71a6fa21-ea62-4f4e-96f2-d80ab13ae7e3"}
